page.title: 14Village of Stourpaine 1
page.content: 1 We walked to Stourpaine and we went around in two groups looking at the buildings. {Names and Numbers.} In the new part of Stourpaine there are only three names. There are twenty names in the old part. Here are some of the names: 'Rose Cottage','Brook Cottage', 'Camion','Calf House','Manor Farm', 'Somhof','Old Church House', 'Hod Cottage','Salopeon','Leaze', 'Stourpaine House'. {Homes, Other Buildings. 1 stable, 1 village hall, 1 pub, 1 sub-Post Office, 1 garage, 1 telephone box, 1 bus shelter. {Roofs.} When we went around Stourpaine we found 19 thatched roofs, 26 slate roofs and 125 tiled roofs on the buildings.
